HEADWORD: Consanguineous
<hw>Con`san*guin"e*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conguineus</ets>; <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>sanguis</ets> blood: cf.
F. <ets>consanguin</ets>. See <er>Sanquine</er>.]</ety> <def>Of the same
blood; related by birth; descended from the same parent or
ancestor.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> consanguine.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

